	<section class="grid align-center page-section">
		<div class="col-2_sm-2_xs-12">
			<h5>WHAT'S NEXT</h5>
		</div>
		<div class="col-7_sm-9">
			<div class="title-headerline"> </div>
		</div>

		<div class="grid align-center">
			<div class="col-7_lg-8_sm-10_xs-12">
				<div class="page-paragraph_block">
					<p>	This project is very much a work-in-progress, and there are a number of steps, deliverables, and additional features I still plan on exploring and creating. <b>The most important next step is user testing</b>. Now that I’ve explored my assumptions and focused my initial ideas and concepts, it’s time to create a low fidelity interactive prototype to test my work so far with real users. This step will now only be important to improve the user experience but also will give me an opportunity to get some feedback on my initial ideas for branding and visual design elements. </p>

					<p>From a feature perspective, I also plan on exploring the the idea of adding genre tags on artists to help organization and filtering, the ability to search for specific songs as well as artists and how that would impact other features, and finally researching the feasibility of syncing or connecting a user to their accounts on their music streaming services of choice which could open up a number of interesting integration possibilities. Looking at the final visual design deliverables, along with creating a low-fi prototype, as part of my final designs I plan on creating some animated high-fidelity designs to capture some micro-animations/interactions for the last layer of design polish. </p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>


